  <title>Introducing OVITO</title>

  <para>
    <informalfigure><screenshot><mediaobject><imageobject>
       <imagedata fileref="images/ovito_screenshot.png" format="PNG" />
    </imageobject></mediaobject></screenshot></informalfigure>

    OVITO is a scientific visualization and analysis software for
    molecular and other particle-based dataset, typically generated by numeric 
    simulation models in materials science, physics and chemistry disciplines.
    OVITO runs on Windows, Linux, and macOS. It is being developed by
    <link xlink:href="https://www.ovito.org">OVITO GmbH</link>, a Germany-based spin-off company founded by the original lead developer 
    <link xlink:href="http://scholar.google.com/citations?user=f8Tw3eEAAAAJ">Dr. Alexander
    Stukowski</link>.
  </para>

  <para>
    The first release of OVITO dates back to 2009 and has been described in
    <link xlink:href="http://stacks.iop.org/0965-0393/18/015012">this paper</link>. 
    Please cite this reference when using OVITO in your research.
  </para>

  <para>
    For further information, please visit the website <link xlink:href="https://www.ovito.org">www.ovito.org</link>.
  </para>

